        "text": "p. 95–96 In communication theory, as we have discussed, the selection understanding is moment of the triad information, communication and understanding. With a somewhat strange twist, Luhmann formulates that \"communication [is] realized when and insofar as understanding comes about.\" This sounds like a conclusion that is hard to imagine in an autopoietic time, especially since any utterance that follows an utterance will have been understanding only if a next utterance takes it up as a communication of information.\n\n– [[Communication (Kommunikation)]]"
